Here, a denotes the ion species, zaq is the charge of the ion, ca0 is the bulk ion concentration. rf is the charge density of the fixed charges, e0 is the permittivity of free space, and c(r) is the electrostatic potential at r. We have developed a three-dimensional finite-difference algorithm to numerically solve nonlinear PB for c(r) and c(r) (55). From c(r), the tightly bound region is quantitatively and unambiguously defined. In Fig. 1, we show
