T as the temperature is increased. For high NaCl concentration, more ions are bound, causing strong charge neutralization. Because the ds helix has much greater charge neutralization than ss helix (coil), as temperature is increased, the increase in the electrostatic interaction in ssDNA is more significant than in dsDNA (see Fig. 4 a), causing a decrease in DGel
