37; the electrostatic component of the helix stability, on the helix length. We use the number of basepairs N to define the helix length. We will also examine how the electrostatics affects the validity of the additive nearest neighbor model for the nucleic acid helix stability (17–23). To focus on the lengthdependence and the additivity effect, we study the electrostatic free energy ‘‘per base stack’’ gel
